## Critical Safety Rules

```text
1. Never delete source code without backup or git checkpoint.
2. Never expose secrets in logs, commits, reports, screenshots, or terminal output.
3. Never hardcode production passwords, Cloudflare tokens, API keys, LINE secrets, JWT secrets, or DB credentials.
4. Generate secure database passwords automatically with cryptographic randomness.
5. Store generated secrets only in gitignored local env files.
6. Do not remove Docker volumes by default.
7. Do not remove active project data.
8. Inspect before changing files.
9. Prefer env variables and .env.example templates over hardcoded values.
10. Prefer scripts that can be re-run safely.
11. Every change must have a verification command.
12. If a destructive operation may affect data, stop and document the risk.
13. If a non-destructive issue is found, make the safest best-effort fix and document it.
14. Do not mark complete until verification commands have run or exact failure reasons are documented.
```

